24/10/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonia and Greece have agreed to launch a new round of UN-mediated negotiations to resolve the issue of Macedonia's official name, according to a joint statement following talks Saturday (23 October) between Macedonian Foreign Minister and her Greek counterpart, Petros Molyviatis, who is on a two-day visit to Skopje.
Molyviatis also met with Macedonian President Branko Crvenkovski and Prime Minister Hari Kostov, as well as with leaders of the main political parties.
He reaffirmed Athens' support for the neighbouring country's bid to join the EU.
(AFP, A1 TV, ANA - 23/10/04)
